[2] New Zealand: unborn babies die
Date: Tue 1 Oct 2019
Source: Otago Daily Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.odt.co.nz/news/national/two-unborn-babies-die-after-mums-catch-measles


Auckland health officials, in their latest update, confirmed 5 pregnant woman have caught measles and 2 of those fetuses died.

Medical officer of health Dr William Rainger said [fewer] cases were presenting each week than when it peaked at the end of August [2019].

Between 35%-40% of people with measles have been hospitalised during February to mid-September [2019] -- much higher than previous outbreaks where only about 10% of those who contract it ended up in hospital.

Between [1 Jan and 26 Sep 2019] there have been 1498 confirmed cases of measles notified across New Zealand, according to the Ministry of Health, with 1246 cases occurring in Auckland.

Double the number of people have been hospitalised with measles than usual.

Bartholomew said about half of those admitted to hospital were children. There was also a much higher number of Maori and Pacific Island people hospitalised than any other ethnicities.

