[The Centers For Disease Control and Prevention said [on Fri 4 Oct 2019] the number of states reporting sick individuals stands at 31. The CDC confirms a total of 1249 cases of measles for the year.

An outbreak is considered 3 or more cases during a period of time in one location. Overall, there have been 22 separate measles outbreaks in 17 states (https://www.wtvm.com/2019/10/05/centers-disease-control-prevention-confirms-highest-number-measles-cases-since/). - Mod.LK

