[4] New York (Putnam County)
Date: Tue 1 Oct 2019 3:47 PM ET
Source: Patch [abridged, edited]
https://patch.com/new-york/southeast/measles-case-putnam-county-more-exposure-possible


The Putnam County Department of Health has confirmed a case of measles.

Several possible exposure sites have been identified [see source URL above for list of possible locations/times of exposure.]

The patient has been isolated to avoid spreading the disease further.

This has been the worst year for measles across the United States since 1992, according to the Centers for Disease Control. As of 26 Sep 2019, the CDC reported 1243 cases of measles confirmed in 31 states.

More than 75% of the cases this year are linked to outbreaks in New York.

Measles is more likely to spread and cause outbreaks in U.S. communities where groups of people are unvaccinated.

Measles can cause serious complications. As of 26 Sep 2019, 131 of the people who got measles this year were hospitalized, and 65 reported having complications, including pneumonia and encephalitis.

These outbreaks are linked to travelers who brought measles back from other countries such as Israel, Ukraine, and the Philippines, where large measles outbreaks are occurring.

The longest running outbreak in the US was in neighboring Rockland County (which started in October 2018). It was declared over last week [week of 23 Sep 2019], as the date of completion of 2 maximum incubation periods (42 days) without cases approached 30 Sep 2019.

[Byline: Lanning Taliaferro]

