[6] New Jersey (Essex County)
Date: Fri 4 Oct 2019
Source: New Jersey 101.5 [abridged, edited]
https://nj1015.com/measles-makes-a-return-to-new-jersey/


Measles has returned to New Jersey, with a case confirmed at an Essex County elementary school.

The recent outbreak in New Jersey, with a total of 19 confirmed cases dating back to October 2018, was mostly in Lakewood and was considered by the state Department of Health to be over as of 16 May 2019. The department's website reported a new case was confirmed on [Tue 1 Oct 2019], but did not disclose a location.

It is the 1st confirmed case since mid-July [2019], according to the agency. "The source of this infection is currently unknown," it wrote.

An email sent by Nutley School Superintendent Dr Julie Glazer to parents on [Thu 3 Oct 2019] said the case at the Washington Elementary School was confirmed by the Nutley Department of Health, according to NorthJersey.com.

In the email, Glazer said the school was thoroughly cleaned by the school's custodial staff.

[Byline: Dan Alexander]

